CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 30, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "On Their Way - T/4 John W. Turnipseed, General Devers' orderly, rides with Councilman Edward Leonard as the motorcade gets under way at the County Airport. Captain Myers was not in automobile when the picture was snapped. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: John W. Turnipseed wearing U. S. Army uniform, and Councilman Edward Leonard, riding in back of convertible car with signs for Turnipseed and Capt. Myers, in parade at airport
